dlDJJFj1ZNXzRQfFeOuZBDTA6y5Wywg9i4OLKtYcPGB1q_MZ8pohk1Uute7nxjxv7bCemOqUc4t=
yVYyrVukfn0taEvc0TM97jy3ufU9u5T00nQTPKgAJw4LLnqoNuXfwDYkkHvwm6zezfZyTr35QmP=
xa74foWWjfT3u2IoZ4Go51W9FftetF7gzAzRsyNqje2NmZApehBKSHpVbNx4QBAmeKkJfvUXPEv=
9AdWdIic], that since we=E2=80=99ve experienced the positives, a remote-fir=
st future is inevitable. My friend, and co-author of this essay, Dan Doyon =
[https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2KwzAMhU9TL4N_4jReeDGbuYZxIiUxdexgK=
1Ny-3HbgQEhIcTj6XuzJ1xzueyRK7FXc3QdaBM-a0QiLOysWFwAKwY5Kt0bBrYHMeqRheqWgrj7=
EC2VE9lxTjHMnkJObwXnUrPN6sUgv8tRLxK8x0UPZjIw34WHwRjgH19_QsA0o8UfLFdOyKLdiI5=
6U183-d2KnuH1UTfnvW2AHuLlcmpuLFjJpeBCKKH0oEwnurjBQ6SaT3Xr-b7Krp5TJT8_XnpWbM=
o05RLS2s6Pze8Y34fG4NrczxTocpj8FBE-ePRJ6Q3sVkxYWnrgPLVsBNf9IIzp9R9O41dCCC6NY=
s0ZclOlf9NfqSuBKg], agrees that remote can and should be the default mode g=
oing forward, but he doesn=E2=80=99t think it=E2=80=99s a given.
Dan's professional profile is somewhat illegible. On one hand, he's spent 1=
5 years in institutional private equity focused on office real estate and c=
urrently runs a forward-thinking company [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/=
eJxFkM2OhSAMhZ_msjT8iMqCxWzmNQhCrxIRDNS58e2H0cUkTdukOT35jrMISy6XPnJF8tcMXgf=
oBJ8aAREKOSsUE7xmA5-E7BXxuvdskhMJ1bwLwG5D1FhOIMc5x-AshpxuBaVcklXzgToGI-v9W8=
hxVqMHodzUNqnG2bvH154-QHKg4QfKlROQqFfEo77E14t_t_rksh3ROlhzPQLaGPDqXN5J0JxyR=
hkTTMhBqI51cfUbSzWf4tXTfeFdPeeK1m23oOiUcc4lpKWdt9XuEO9DIzBt7mdqvw0kO0fwDxw-=
Gd24ZoEEpWXnjcWWDKOyH5hSvaQPTKMXjDHKlSDN2eemSv-mv6zggKg] in the sector. On =
the other hand, he's lived nomadically for the past 5 years and built one o=
f my favorite consumer software products, Readwise [https://email.mg2.subst=
ack.com/c/eJxFULtuxCAQ_JqjtHg6pqBIc7-BsFnb6DBYsOTkvw85F5FWs8VoNI_FIWy5XObMF=
ckfWLxOMAneNQIiFNIqFBu8YSOfhJKaeCM9m9REQrVrAThciAZLA3K2OYbFYcjpo6CUK7KbeVqV=
9l9CU8X8xCVfFy3GEdwsVrkKfvu65gOkBQz8QLlyAhLNjnjWh_h-8Ge_As6_Q4UhZBIMp5xRxgQ=
TahR6YEPc_Yulmpt4SHpsfKhtruiW17DkgxSTMs65hLR1-rW7A-KH6KFt_0dLAS8Lyc0R_N0H71=
k-De0GCUqfy1uHfQxGlRyZ1lLRO38vLBhjlGtBurPPXZX-TX8BPDF62w]. As a result of t=
hat bizarre mashup, he's thought more about both the future of office and r=
emote work than most will in a lifetime.=C2=A0
After I hit send on the original piece, Dan did two things:=C2=A0
Introduced me to Flo, who he said was building the best virtual HQ product =
he=E2=80=99s used.
Helped me appreciate an important nuance: remote work is not necessarily in=
evitable.=C2=A0
Despite the obvious societal benefits of a remote-first world, he thinks We=
're Never Going Back should have been more accurately titled We Might Be Go=
ing Back, and that it=E2=80=99s imperative that we collectively do somethin=
g about it. Now is our window of opportunity.=C2=A0
Dan argues that while we have known about the benefits of remote work, both=
 societally and for employers and employees, for half a century, we=E2=80=
=99ve been stuck in an inadequate equilibrium for decades.=C2=A0
What makes an equilibrium inadequate, a fruit that seems to hang tantalizin=
gly low and yet somehow our civilization isn=E2=80=99t plucking, is when th=
ere=E2=80=99s a better stable state and we haven=E2=80=99t reached it.
We know that remote gives us two weeks per year back in commute times, that=
 it is more inclusive, both geographically and demographically, that it giv=
es employers access to better talent, and even that it=E2=80=99s good for t=
he environment. But there are powerful forces in favor of in-office work:
Office landlords who would really like this whole work-from-home-thing to b=
e temporary [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkcGurCAMhp9m2GEo4EQXLM7mv=
IZBqUoGwQBe49vfOi5OQij5S_s3XydbcUn5Mnsqld3XUK8dTcSzBKwVMzsK5sE7A2_ZqVb3zBnt=
oGs75sswZ8TN-mBqPpDtxxj8ZKtP8VshhGzZavSoRKelGi24TthZdkKDxl6B6zX06vG1h_MYJzT=
4D_OVIrJg1lr38lI_L_lL5zzPZgwpbSPmpZnSRto9KIUZbT0y3k8ppOAgOXRPml8pf_jk68ULT_=
PsJ-QnSZgLtxn5QlY82OhCyu6RSjqi83HhdUVug80b84b6ggBQoNq36htowuo-EOmvemmxLbIpx=
1iqnT73aCybmOqYMrWh9Ge1G4ZvgiANFLcj0kgDRjsGdA-_-qzhS3RYMGKm9bjBVoIPotVv6Hvd=
iocXAVYAICQBJGeXqCr-mf4HUvWhaQ]
Ex-Yahoo! CEO Marissa Meyer who claim [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx=
FUsuO3CAQ_Br7hsXDzNgHDlF2I-UTcrIwtMdkbLCg2dn5-2B8iISaoqu7S63CaIRHiG91hITtGS=
Z8H6A8vNIGiBDbnCBOzip244OQ_dha1Vs2yKF1aVoiwK7dpjBmaI88b85odMHXDkq5bFe12LuQk=
rORDQbuY8-lNP1shC3TZH9jl67O1oE3oOAL4jt4aDe1Ih6pET8a_qscXMEEX9hUJToT9pJ1mIgP=
SP7mhKSUEJfCVgvIK8Sn8w-yxLCTNexAVp1IyvGILp2EDS-fnIVEGL2znjZcnGr3zxIRvrERH79=
